comments: Edwards (BKN) applies a stayed forearm to Garland's (CLE) side and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Aldridge (BKN) briefly places his hand to Allen's (CLE) front as he gathers the ball and immediately removes his hand as he releases his pass.
Garland (CLE) dislodges the ball from Edwards (BKN) after gathering the rebound. Any ensuing contact is deemed incidental.
Irving (BKN) and Okoro (CLE) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Aldridge (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and does not deliver contact.
Mobley (CLE) jumps vertically and legally contests Irving's (BKN) driving shot attempt.  Any ensuing arm contact after Irving has released his shot attempt is considered marginal.
Mills (BKN) cleanly deflects the ball away from Mobley (CLE).
Markkanen (CLE) places his forearm to Harden's (BKN) front during his drive to the basket and the contact is marginal.
Harden (BKN) and Markkanen (CLE) briefly engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Aldridge (BKN) is already in Okoro's (CLE) path and he absorbs the contact to his upper body prior to any leg to leg contact.

slides it off. The contact is marginal.
Markkanen (CLE) is retreating alongside Harden's (BKN) path to the basket and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Okoro (CLE) and Irving (BKN) come together at the same spot and incidental foot to foot contact occurs on the perimeter.
